    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>Almost verbatim from the manual: </p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">compare_weights</span>(<span class="hljs-params"><span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span></span>) </span>{ 
    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;weight == <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;weight) {
        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-number">0</span>;
    } 
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> (<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;weight &lt; <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;weight) ? -<span class="hljs-number">1</span> : <span class="hljs-number">1</span>;
} 

<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$unsortedObjectArray</span>, <span class="hljs-string">'compare_weights'</span>);
</code></pre>

<p>If you want objects to be able to sort themselves, see example 3 here: <a href="http://php.net/usort" rel="noreferrer">http://php.net/usort</a></p>
    </div>
