            <div class="comment-body js-comment-edit-hide">
                
                <span class="comment-copy">That third example is basically saying, "Sorry there is no standard way for an object to have a comparator, just write a <code>cmp_obj</code> static function in the object, and remember to call usort with that function." Okay, except that cmp_obj has no special meaning in PHP. Maybe that would be useful if PHP had something like Python's <code>__cmp__</code> function as standard, or Java's <code>implements Comparable</code> interface so it could sort and use <code>&lt;</code>, <code>&gt;</code>, comparators without digging into whatever that class's implementation wants the sort to be. Unfortunately it looks like this isn't changing in PHP7 either.</span>
                
                <div class="d-inline-flex ai-center">
– <a href="/users/778234/nobugs" title="9,314 reputation" class="comment-user">NoBugs</a>
