<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="125065">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>Depending on the problem you are trying to solve, you may also find the SPL interfaces useful. For example, implementing the ArrayAccess interface would allow you to access your class like an array. Also, implementing the SeekableIterator interface would let you loop through your object just like an array. This way you could sort your object just as if it were a simple array, having full control over the values it returns for a given key.</p>
<p>For more details:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://devzone.zend.com/article/2565-The-Standard-PHP-Library-SPL" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Zend Article</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.phpriot.com/articles/oop-with-spl-php-5/2" rel="nofollow noreferrer">PHPriot Article</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.php.net/manual/en/book.spl.php" rel="nofollow noreferrer">PHP Manual</a></li>
</ul>
    </div>
